  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F.",
    "Marinate barramundi in soy sauce for at least 20 minutes.",
    "Heat oil in a wok or large skillet over medium-high heat.",
    "Add garlic and red pepper flakes, cook until fragrant (about 1 minute).",
    "Place marinated barramundi into the hot pan, searing on both sides for about 5 minutes per side.",
    "Remove fish from wok, then add lime leaves and sprinkle soy sauce over the top.",
    "Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until liquid is absorbed (about 2-3 minutes).",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro before serving."
